<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF0FFEEE1FD00CDFD99FF73" authority="Gaede, 1930" authorityName="Gaede" authorityYear="1930" box="[199,570,150,177]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="phoebe" subSpecies="almana">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF0FFEEE1FD00CDFE01FF72" bold="true" box="[199,418,150,177]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">M. phoebe almana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF0FFEEE09000CCFD99FF73" author="Gaede, M." box="[426,570,150,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" pagination="203 - 217" refId="ref9102" refString="Gaede, M. (1930) Melitaea. In: Seitz A (Ed.), Grossschmetterlinge de Erde, Die Palaearctische Schmetterlinge. Supplement, Alfred Kernen, Stuttgart, 203 - 217. [16 plates]" type="book chapter" year="1930">Gaede, 1930</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1BD8652DFFF0FFEEE37800CDFBF2FEA7" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="537D36A6FFF0FFEEE37800CDFBF2FEA7" blockId="8.[151,1437,150,2013]" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">
[TL: 
<collectingCountry id="2BD57636FFF0FFEEE34400CCFD1FFF73" box="[638,700,150,176]" name="Syria" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">Syria</collectingCountry>
, Elman Dagh], following 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF0FFEEE2DF00CCFA91FF73" author="Russell, PJ &amp; Tennent, W. J." box="[997,1330,150,177]" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" pagination="27 - 56" refId="ref10922" refString="Russell, PJ. C. &amp; Tennent, W. J. (2016) A synonymic list of names associated with western Palaearctic Melitaea phoebe (Denis &amp; Schiffermuller, 1775) species group taxa M. phoebe; M. punica Oberthur, 1876; M. ornata Christoph, 1893) (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae). Nota Lepidopterologica, 39 (1), 27 - 56. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / nl. 39.5929" type="journal article" year="2016">Russell &amp; Tennent (2016: 44</bibRefCitation>
, note 14) this name is a 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF0FFEEE00C00E1FE77FF17" box="[310,468,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">nomen nudum</emphasis>
. It was described by Gaede as follows: ‘a pale 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF0FFEEE2D300E1FBF7FF17" box="[1001,1108,186,213]" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="from">race from</taxonomicName>
North 
<collectingCountry id="2BD57636FFF0FFEEE59900E0FB7DFF17" box="[1187,1246,186,212]" name="Syria" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">Syria</collectingCountry>
similar to 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF0FFEEE46C00E0FF4AFF3B" authority="Fruhst." authorityName="Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1908" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="telona">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF0FFEEE46C00E0FA3FFF17" box="[1366,1436,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">telona</emphasis>
Fruhst.
</taxonomicName>
’ (Translation). Although 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF0FFEEE33B0084FD71FF3B" author="Gaede, M." box="[513,722,222,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" pagination="203 - 217" refId="ref9102" refString="Gaede, M. (1930) Melitaea. In: Seitz A (Ed.), Grossschmetterlinge de Erde, Die Palaearctische Schmetterlinge. Supplement, Alfred Kernen, Stuttgart, 203 - 217. [16 plates]" type="book chapter" year="1930">Gaede (1930: 208)</bibRefCitation>
attributed the name to Rebel (undated), no description by Rebel or anyone else has been found. 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF0FFEEE3390158FCC6FEDF" author="Hesselbarth, G. &amp; van Oorschot, H. &amp; Wagener, S." box="[515,869,258,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" pagination="1 - 847" refId="ref9287" refString="Hesselbarth, G., van Oorschot, H. &amp; Wagener, S. (1995) Die Tagfalter der Turkei unter Berucksichtigung der angrenzenden Lander, Sigbert Wagener, Bocholt, Germany, 1, 1 - 757, 2, 758 - 1354, 3, 1 - 847." type="journal article" year="1995">
Hesselbarth 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF0FFEEE3AA0159FD60FEDF" box="[656,707,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">et al</emphasis>
. (1995: 1031)
</bibRefCitation>
suggested that it may have been a misspelling of 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF0FFEEE1AD017DFF54FE83" box="[151,247,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">amanica</emphasis>
Rebel, but Gaede treated the names separately. As far as the authors are aware there has not been any illustration of “almana” and it was not mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF0FFEEE3D00111FBEEFEA7" author="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G." box="[746,1101,330,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" refId="ref11693" refString="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G. (2014) The genus Melitaea Fabricius, 1807 (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae, Nymphalinae) Taxonomy and systematics with special reference to the male genitalia. Tshikolovets publications, Pardubice, Czech Republic, 360 pp." type="book" year="2014">van Oorschot &amp; Coutsis (2014)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
